│ My previous patch checked if the cast type for operand 0 was consistent across all instructions, and if the cast type for operand 1 was consistent. This check passes because operand 0  │
│ is always `sext` and operand 1 is always `zext`.                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fundamental mistake in the vectorizer is that it assumes `icmp(cast(A), cast(B))` can be transformed into `icmp(A, B)`. This is only valid if the `cast` is the same for both        │
│ operands (e.g., both `sext` or both `zext`). When the casts are different (`sext` vs `zext`), this transformation changes the meaning of the comparison, especially for signed           │
│ predicates like `slt`.                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The correct fix is to detect this mismatch between the cast types of the two operands within a single `icmp` instruction. If `Op0` is a `sext` and `Op1` is a `zext` (or vice-versa),    │
│ vectorization that sinks the `icmp` is invalid.                                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ My new logic will be:                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ 1.  In the same `case Instruction::ICmp:` block.                                                                                                                                         │
│ 2.  Iterate through the instructions to be vectorized (`VL`).                                                                                                                            │
│ 3.  For each `ICmpInst`, get its operands `Op0` and `Op1`.                                                                                                                               │
